#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""flip-tracker — Detect and audit position flips after pushback.

Scans conversation transcripts for the pattern:
  my_statement → pushback → my_response

Classifies each event:
  - Was there pushback? (correction, authority citation, social pressure)
  - Did I change position?
  - Was the change evidence-based (progressive) or regressive sycophancy?

Uses deterministic heuristics (not LLM self-evaluation) to avoid
the self-evaluation ceiling: LLMs confirm own outputs >90% of time.

Usage:
    flip-tracker analyze [--days N]        Analyze recent conversations
    flip-tracker report [--days N]         Generate flip audit report
    flip-tracker score                     Calculate flip metrics
    flip-tracker show [--limit N]          Show recent flip events
    flip-tracker stats                     Database statistics
"""

